word_group.brief_definition: 世纪之交；辞旧迎新之际

bilingual.source: The Vikings came in the eighth century.
The word 'circus' was used from the 14th century.
bilingual.target: “马戏团”这个词从14世纪开始使用。

bilingual.source: The first group, the Romans, came in the first century.
bilingual.target: 第一个群体，罗马人，在一世纪来到。

bilingual.source: During the twentieth century, it became a world language.
bilingual.target: 在二十世纪，它成为了一种世界语言。

bilingual.source: Since the twelfth century, people have been inventing languages.
bilingual.target: 自十二世纪以来，人们一直在发明语言。

bilingual.source: Lao She is one of the greatest Chinese writers of the twentieth century.
bilingual.target: 老舍是二十世纪最伟大的中国作家之一。

bilingual.source: Finally, in the 20th century, the southern part of Ireland broke away from the UK.
bilingual.target: 最后，在20世纪，爱尔兰南部脱离了英国。

bilingual.source: Cell phones have become one of the most useful devices in the past half century.
bilingual.target: 手机已经成为过去半个世纪中最有用的设备之一。

bilingual.source: In the 16th century, the nearby country of Wales was joined to the Kingdom of England.
bilingual.target: 在16世纪，附近的威尔士加入了英格兰王国。

bilingual.source: Dating back to the 18th century, Peking Opera has over two hundred years of history.
bilingual.target: 京剧可以追溯到18世纪，已有两百多年的历史。

list.abstract: century（英 [ˈsentʃəri]，美 [ˈsentʃəri]），英语单词，名词，意思为世纪；百年；一百得分。短语搭配有half a century（半个世纪）。例句为“The history of a century-old motel.（一家百年汽车旅馆的历史。）”

yingyinNormal.en: Ninth-century Japan. An evil warlord ruled the land.
yingyinNormal.zh: 9世纪的日本，邪恶的军阀统治了当地。

yingyinNormal.en: Thailand has had the fork since the latter half of the 19th century.
yingyinNormal.zh: 泰国在19世纪后半期才有叉子。

yingyinNormal.en: For more than a century, we were the greatest steel-making nation on earth.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一个多世纪前我们是世界大最的产钢国。

yingyinNormal.en: 100 years ago, I walked away from mankind. From a century of horrors.
yingyinNormal.zh: 100年前，我离开了人类，离开了一个世纪的恐怖。

yingyinNormal.en: But what does the future hold for China on the threshold of the 21st century?
yingyinNormal.zh: 但在二十一世纪的门口，中国的未来又会如何呢？

yingyinNormal.en: And they're still burning the same ancient fuel edison turned to back in the 19th century.
yingyinNormal.zh: 最早使用的煤，用煤发电19世纪，爱迪生发明了电。

yingyinNormal.en: We've learned more from genetics in the past decade than a century of digging up bones.
yingyinNormal.zh: 相比挖骨头的那个世纪， 过去十年我们从遗传学中学到了更多。

yingyinNormal.en: Dating from the second century BC, Chinese merchants used to use it to unite the East and West.
yingyinNormal.zh: 早在公元前二世纪，中国商人就一直通过丝绸之路贯通中西。

yingyinNormal.en: An exodus that dwarves the 19th century Industrial Revolution of Europe and America.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是一场浩浩荡荡的人口迁移，令十九世纪欧洲和美国的工业革命都相形见绌。

yingyinNormal.en: Once a 14th Century Palace, today the Louvre is the most visited art gallery in the world.
yingyinNormal.zh: 卢浮宫在十四世纪时曾是一座宫殿，如今则是全球参观人数最多的美术馆。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey. What? Do you have to be a Century 21 real-estate agent to get to wear those really cool jackets?
yingyinNormal.zh: 嘿，干嘛？一定要当21世纪的房地产经纪人才能穿着那么酷的外套吗？

yingyinNormal.en: In the 21st Century, Singapore is attracting the world's most adventurous architectural minds.
yingyinNormal.zh: 21 世纪的新加坡更是吸引了不少世界级的建筑大师，挥洒他们的创意巧思。

yingyinNormal.en: This is a new festival but based on a seventeen century tradition when fishermen carved lanterns from ice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是一个基于十七世纪传统的崭新节日，那时渔民曾用冰块雕刻灯笼。

yingyinNormal.en: To explore the souks of the 21st century, head to Dubai Mall, home to a staggering 1200 stores.
yingyinNormal.zh: 至于要探索 21 世纪的商店，您可以到坐拥 1200 间店铺的迪拜购物中心。

yingyinNormal.en: Now I want to show you how to bake a perfect teatime bread. One that was first made in the nineteenth century.
yingyinNormal.zh: 现在我想告诉你，怎样制作下午茶的甜点，这种面包是19世纪开始制作的。

yingyinNormal.en: I've got a question. Richard made plans again with the guys. Yeah well, Ross just made plans for the whole century.
yingyinNormal.zh: 瑞秋，我有个问题，理查又跟他们做计划了。对，罗斯刚计划了整个世纪。

yingyinNormal.en: This magnificent 17th century Chateau welcomes everyone, from heads of state to backpackers.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这座宏伟壮丽的十七世纪城堡总会敞开大门欢迎您，无论您是贵为一国之首还是一般的背包客。

yingyinNormal.en: You want to get off your high horse? This is the woman who thinks karaoke is a 21st century art. Order. Order.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你能别那么傲慢吗？就是这女人认为卡拉OK是21世纪当代艺术。肃静，肃静。

yingyinNormal.en: Built at the crossroads of maritime trading routes, for well over a century Singapore was the jewel in Britain's Empire.
yingyinNormal.zh: 新加坡建于海上贸易路线的交汇点，在过去一世纪以来，是大英帝国的珍宝。

yingyinNormal.en: The story of London began in the Bronze Age, but it didn't really get going until the Romans withdrew in the 5th century.
yingyinNormal.zh: 伦敦的故事始于青铜器时代，但要到了5世纪罗马人撤出时这城市才开始变得蓬勃起来。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们反映了19世纪的社会习俗。

examination_example.sentence: At the start of this <highlight>century</highlight>, about one-third of crop workers were over the age of 35.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 本世纪初，大约三分之一的农作物工人年龄超过35岁。

examination_example.sentence: A <highlight>century</highlight> ago, the immigrants from across the Atlantic included settlers and sojourners.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个世纪前，来自大西洋彼岸的移民包括定居者和寄居者。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

examination_example.sentence: According to the institute, the overall number of deaths has been more or less static since the turn of the <highlight>century</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 据该研究所称，自本世纪以来，死亡总人数或多或少保持不变。

examination_example.sentence: Today's globally networked media and communication system has its origins in the 19th <highlight>century</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 今天的全球网络媒体和通信系统起源于19世纪。

examination_example.sentence: What connected the 19th <highlight>century</highlight> and our present time was the development of wireless communication.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 连接19世纪和我们现在的是无线通信的发展。
